DT_DrillMaster.DrillName: ABANDON SHIP DRILL-LOWERING L/B TO EMBARKATION DECK
DT_DrillMaster.OfficeGuideLines:
All enclosed life boats must be launched in water and manoeuvered once in 3 months during abandonship drill.
During every abandonship drill, all crew must be seated in the life boat and strap themselves. The drill must be a live drill except for actual launching.
EXCEPTION - MARSHALL ISLAND FLAG VESSELS : CARRY OUT ABANDONSHIP AND FIRE DRILL EVERY WEEK.

DT_DrillMaster.DrillName: LAUNCHING IN WATER & MANOEUVRING (NOTE 1)-ENCLOSED LIFE BOAT(PORT)
DT_DrillMaster.OfficeGuideLines: For launching of boats and maneuvring carry out Risk Assessment and send to the office for approval. Obtain Port Permission as part of the RA.

DT_DrillMaster.DrillName: LAUNCHING IN WATER & MANOEUVRING (NOTE 1)-ENCLOSED LIFE BOAT(STBD)
DT_DrillMaster.OfficeGuideLines: For launching of boats and maneuvring carry out Risk Assessment and send to the office for approval. Obtain Port Permission as part of the RA.
All Free Fall life boats must be launched either by free fall method with only operating crew or by secondary launching methods with or without operating crew.

DT_DrillMaster.DrillName: FREE FALL LIFE BOAT - SIMULATION LAUNCH (NOTE 3)
DT_DrillMaster.OfficeGuideLines: All Free Fall life boats must be launched either by free fall method with only operating crew or by secondary launching methods with or without operating crew.
Dedicated Rescue boat to be lowered and manouvered in Water every month. If the RB us one of the ships lifeboat then it must be lowered in water every 3 months.
